Agropyron cristatum

   [2919.jpg]
    Authority   (L.) Gaertner
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names crested wheatgrass, agropiro de crista
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 2919

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A tufted bunchgrass reaching a height of up to 60 cm.
   USES Used for regrassing abandoned and depleted croplands, and used for
   pasture. KILLING T Very frost resistant. GROWING PERIOD Long-lived
   perennial. Productive stands can be up to 20-35 years old. COMMON NAMES
   Crested wheatgrass (Fairway), Fairway crested wheatgrass. FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: Bromus cristatum. Have certain winter requirements.
   In the subtropics the plant is adapted to altitudes between 1500-2800
   m.

   Sources
   SOURCES (A. cristatum (L.) Gaertn.)
   Kernick M 1978 pp 35-61 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, DRA, FER, PH, USE]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 74 [USE]
   Maas E 1990 pp 276 [SAL]
   Kernick M 1961 pp 38 291 [KTMP]
   Heath M 1985 pp 170-173 [RAIN, KTMP, DRA, DEP, TEXT, SAL]
   Duke J 1975 pp 5 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Shing T 1992 pp 305 [KTMP, TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, DEP, PH, FER, LIG]

